title: Uneasy Money - P.G. Wodehouse   (Unabridged)
description:
Audio Books : Humor : Other quality : English


Unabridged and read by Simon Vance. 6 hours 20 mins duration. MP3CD. ( 48 kbps / 44 kHz Mono, Fraunhofer CBR, jetAudio 8+).





[1917] Lord Dawlish (aka Bill to his friends) is a well-liked and generous man. And poor! Indeed, with only a single exception,he is the poorest of his rank in the British Isles. It's a good thing therefore that he has two simple treasures in life: golfand his fiancee, Claire Fenwick. When she refuses to marry a man of only modest means, it stands to reason that he must go to where the money is and so Bill, in a moment of blinding inspiration, decides to go to America to seek his fortune. But even before he has left he receives the news that he is to inherit a million pounds. Problem solved isn't it?


Enjoy and Seed!!
